Went here on a Tuesday 10/09/18 night I had forgot to buy a cake for my father inlaw and it was 10pm so I looked this place up cause I heard was open 24hrs I called to see if they sold cakes they did ...so I rushed here Frist i live very far so this a 35min drive...I purchased a tresleches cake and 3 conchas  the bread had just come out the oven was nice and hot ....the problem was the cake it look good but when we cut into in was nasty was very very dry it seem like it was old I so embarrassed  to even had bought that cake literally it seem like it was just sitting on a pile off milk usually those cakes are very moist . .but I guess it's my fault I should off ask if it was fresh and I should off known since there was no date when it was made or expiration I so disappointed  we literally ate3 slices and the rest well you know were it ended up in the trash money wasted I will never buy a cake from here ...ever again disgusted

Markellos is my favorite place in Chicago! You cannot go wrong with anything in Markellos. Cheese danishes are amazing, the fresh bread comes out every 15 minutes and they're perfect for sandwiches, muffins are soft and light, and there's too much to choose from (which no one ever can complain about). Everything is fresh and hot and it's cheap! You will be lucky to have any pastries left by the time you get home. I highly recommend this place for anyone whether it's 5am or 5pm!

24 hour latin bakery in my neighborhood. It's convenient, open all the time and has decent pastries. My granddaughter had a birthday recently, and she needed 31 cupcakes for class. I told her I would bring them, and I placed an order here for them 36 hours in advance. So I go to pick them up, and they have 36 muffins ready for me, all packaged up in plastic containers.  Well I asked for cupcakes though. After some discussions, I took the muffins and went on my merry way. Luckily enough, the kids loved them, and they were a big hit.
